article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 64, Texas-Pan American 51
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Kevin Palmer and Justin Reynolds each scored 15 points and Demond Watt added a double-double as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi defeated Texas-Pan American 66-51 Monday night. Palmer reached double figures for the 41st straight game, tying the school record, and Watt finished with 14 points and 13 rebounds for and the Islanders (11-8), who ran their winning streak to six. Matt Mierzycki led the Broncs (3-18) with 14 points. Corpus Christi opened the second half on a 14-5 run to build their largest lead, 46-23. A 3-pointer by ChaRunn Jones cut Pan American's deficit to 58-46 with less than four minutes to play, but the Broncs never got any closer. The Islanders ended the first half on a 19-4 run for a 32-18 halftime lead.
